I don't give five stars lightly but this place deserves it.
Went with a group of 8 family in town, old folks, little kids, etc.
Everybody was very pleased.
We had the best friday fish fry I've ever had in Phoenix.
Fish was fresh, fries fresh, beer cold, my son had a chicken breast dish that was outstanding, perfectly cooked.
Service was excellent and a guy playing guitar not too loud was fun.
We were placed out on the patio which wasn't my first choice with my elderly mom in town, but it turned out terrific and nice fun atmosphere.
Manager or owner came by to check if we were having a good time.
In the Anthem area right now I'd say this is probably the best bar food/casual dining place you can get.
Not lightning fast food service because I think everything's fresh, but the place was packed and we didn't wait more than about 15 minutes for food.

